The tragic shooting at Columbine High School left 15 dead, including the gunmen.
Confusion over the death toll arose due to overlapping areas covered by SWAT teams.
Despite fear and intense security, students wanted to return to school.
The community, both local and nationwide, rallied in support.
Politicians like Pat Buchanan and Al Gore called for change and unity.
As Columbine students prepare to return to class, the healing process continues with a focus on coming together and honoring the victims.
Love and support are seen as essential in the face of such senseless violence.
